This paper discusses the evaluation of dialogue systems, which falls under the category of natural language processing and computational linguistics (cs.CL). The study also involves human judgments and user experience, which suggests a potential fit for human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The use of automated metrics and experimentation also suggests a potential fit for artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the study involves the analysis of data and the identification of factors that impact consistency and agreement, which suggests a potential fit for information retrieval (cs.IR).
